@startuml
title Elastic Disk Provisioning Architecture - Thin-Provisioning Flow

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

actor "Cloud Consumer" as CC
participant "Provisioning\nSystem" as Prov
participant "Hypervisor" as HV
participant "Dynamic Disk\nAllocation Component\n(thin-provisioning program)" as TPP
participant "Virtual Server" as VS
database "Cloud Storage" as STO
participant "Pay-Per-Use\nMonitor" as PPM

CC -> Prov : (1) request virtual server\n(e.g., 3 x 150 GB disks)
Prov -> HV : begin VM provisioning
HV -> HV : (2) hard disks chosen as\ndynamic / thin-provisioned
HV -> TPP : (3) call dynamic disk\nallocation component
TPP -> STO : (4) create thin disks\nin near-zero size folder
STO --> VS : disks attached\n(max = 450 GB,\nactual used = 0 GB)

== Runtime usage grows ==
VS -> STO : write data (apps, files)
STO -> STO : folder grows with use

PPM -> STO : (5) track actual\ndynamically allocated storage
PPM -> CC : granular billing data

note right of TPP
  Thin-provisioning software is installed
  on virtual servers to process dynamic
  storage allocation via the hypervisor.
end note

@enduml
